init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They were left to their own devices and decided to explore space instead.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The rest of the world should have done the same.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Was it a fear of the Americans?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The first and primary planet they decided to move to was Mars.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: America was becoming an interstellar nation.
